{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"``` javascript\nlight.intensity = 0;\n```\n\nor \n\n``` javascript\nlight.color.setRGB( 0, 0, 0 );\n```\n\nor \n\n``` javascript\nscene.remove( light );\n```\n","created_at":"2012-05-20T00:13:45.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945#issuecomment-5805734","id":5805734,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4MDU3MzQ=","updated_at":"2012-05-20T00:13:45.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/5805734","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/438022?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/alteredq","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzODAyMg==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"alteredq","type":"User","id":438022,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"`scene.remove` may be the best solution, because as far as I know the graphic card supports maximum 8lights in one time.\n\nWhy isn't available the `light.visible` property in the WebGL renderer? For example if I want to turn on and off lights frequently, then changing the `light.visible` property would be smarter and faster, than add and remove it again and again.\n","created_at":"2012-05-21T13:43:04.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945#issuecomment-5822699","id":5822699,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4MjI2OTk=","updated_at":"2012-05-21T13:43:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/5822699","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1734965?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arkasia","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MzQ5NjU=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arkasia","type":"User","id":1734965,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arkasia\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Performance-wise these are practically equivalent. \n\nIn WebGL majority of costs come from shaders and for these to change you would need to rebuild the programs in all your materials (this comes with a cost though):\n\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/wiki\/Updates\n\nSo this is more of the matter of API aesthetics. \n\n@mrdoob what do you think - should `light.visible` turn on \/ off light casting?\n\nSome other things that come to mind with `light.visible` instead of turning on \/ off lights would be showing \/ hiding of light helpers or toggling of volumetric lights.\n","created_at":"2012-05-21T16:48:12.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945#issuecomment-5827497","id":5827497,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4Mjc0OTc=","updated_at":"2012-05-21T16:48:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/5827497","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/438022?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/alteredq","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzODAyMg==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"alteredq","type":"User","id":438022,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> @mrdoob what do you think - should light.visible turn on \/ off light casting?\n\nUh, I wasn't aware of this behaviour :) It's a side effect of the lights being part of the scene graph update. But I think it makes sense, and it allows you to switch off lights without being destructive with the color\/intensity values. I think it's good API wise.\n","created_at":"2012-05-21T17:33:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945#issuecomment-5828673","id":5828673,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1945","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4Mjg2NzM=","updated_at":"2012-05-21T17:33:59.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/5828673","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> Uh, I wasn't aware of this behaviour :) It's a side effect of the lights being part of the scene graph update.\n\nHaha. Ok, implemented.\n\nFinally it turns out we already had something very similar with `light.onlyShadow` property though I guess it's better to keep also this as such shadow-only casting lights are logically different from turned off lights (for example their scen